& [HandoffAwareProofRunnerDesign] is the design contract for consuming approved proof handoff evidence
  @ [proof_handoff_design] coordination/manager_reviewed_proof_handoff_design.sop
  @ [worker_runner_design] coordination/worker_runner_design.sop
  @ [record_models] src/negotiated_agent/worker_lifecycle.py and src/negotiated_agent/worker_runner.py
  @ [manager_job_notice] coordination/manager_job_notice.sop
  @ [created_at] 2026-05-29T22:07:00Z

  + [design_status] is ready_for_implementation_slice
  + [authority_boundary] is handoff_aware_proof_runner_design_not_command_execution
  + [primary_goal] is define how the existing proof-command runner consumes an approved ManagerProofHandoffRecord
  + [non_goal] is autonomous worker implementation execution
  + [non_goal] is target workspace mutation
  + [non_goal] is mailbox read cursor advancement
  + [non_goal] is Manager frontier advancement
  + [non_goal] is proof command selection outside handoff evidence

& [ConsumptionInputs] is what the proof runner must receive
  + [required_ref] is ManagerProofHandoffRecord with handoff_status approved
  + [required_ref] is ready_for_proof WorkerCycleRecord referenced by ready_cycle_ref
  + [required_ref] is ExecutionGateDecision referenced by execution_gate_ref
  + [required_arg] is requested proof command
  + [required_arg] is current_frontier
  + [required_arg] is worker_uuid
  + [authority_boundary] is approved_handoff_not_completion_approval
  = must: validate handoff using validate_manager_proof_handoff before running any command
  = must: reject when requested command differs from handoff proof_command
  = must: reject when current_frontier differs from frontier_at_handoff
  = must: reject when worker_uuid differs from handoff or ready cycle

& [ProofExecutionBehavior] is the allowed command execution path
  + [runner_function] is run_worker_proof_command
  + [command] is ManagerProofHandoffRecord.proof_command
  + [cycle_id] is new proof result cycle id, not the ready cycle id
  + [claim_refs] is inherited from the ready_for_proof WorkerCycleRecord
  + [slice_ref] is inherited from the ready_for_proof WorkerCycleRecord
  + [proof_refs] is ready_cycle_ref, handoff_ref, execution_gate_ref, and command proof ref
  + [changed_files] is none unless a later proof-specific protocol designs generated proof artifacts
  + [authority_boundary] is proof_result_cycle_not_manager_approval
  = must: leave the ready_for_proof cycle unchanged
  = must: write failed proof evidence through WorkerFailureRecord on nonzero command return
  = must: return nonzero on failed proof

& [ForbiddenSideEffects] is what handoff consumption must not do
  - never: execute implementation work
  - never: apply or rollback target workspace files
  - never: advance mailbox read cursors
  - never: mutate active conversation current_frontier
  - never: mark Manager work slice completed
  - never: overwrite ready cycle or handoff artifacts

& [ProofExpectations] is the minimum implementation proof for this design
  + [test_case] is approved handoff runs a harmless proof command and writes a new completed WorkerCycleRecord
  + [test_case] is failed handoff proof writes WorkerFailureRecord and failed_proof cycle evidence
  + [test_case] is command mismatch fails before running the command
  + [test_case] is non-ready source cycle fails before running the command
  + [test_case] is ready cycle and handoff artifacts remain unchanged

& [ImplementationOrder] is the safe next split
  + [slice_1] is add loaders for ManagerProofHandoffRecord and handoff-aware proof runner helper
  + [slice_2] is add CLI mode to consume approved handoff refs
  + [slice_3] is add operator docs and checkpoint
  + [slice_4] is refresh spec audit before considering run-local implementation execution
